Modified assets/prompts.txt to replace and append a large set of prompts, removing creative writing prompts and adding factual and trivia-style questions.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Update module versions in SLURM HPC scripts

All SLURM scripts now use updated module versions: gcc/14.2.0, python-scientific/3.10.8-foss-2022b, cuda/12.8.0, and cudnn/9.10.1.4-cuda-12.8.0. The purge command is simplified and the cudnn module path is adjusted for consistency.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Add hierarchical G3_U5 performance results and update slurm scripts

Added new performance results and summary for hierarchical G3_U5 multiuser evaluation. Updated multiple slurm HPC scripts to support recent evaluation changes and improvements.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Update SLURM scripts for Volta V100 GPU nodes

Changed SLURM job scripts to use the 'volta-gpu' partition, added V100 GPU constraints, and specified GPU resource requests for V100. This ensures jobs are scheduled on the correct hardware and improves compatibility with the current HPC cluster configuration.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Refactor Huggingface cache env vars in SLURM scripts

Updated environment variable assignments in SLURM scripts to use $HF_HOME for cache directories, improving maintainability. Added a dummy notebook file.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Update module loads in all slurm HPC scripts

Changed module purge to use --force, switched GCC version from 14.2.0 to 12.2.0, and added python/3.10.8 to all slurm_scripts. This ensures consistent environment setup and compatibility across all HPC job scripts.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Remove python-scientific module from slurm scripts

Eliminated the 'module load python-scientific/3.10.8-foss-2022b' line from all relevant slurm HPC scripts to streamline environment setup and avoid unnecessary module loading.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Update hierarchical multiuser performance results

Added new performance results and summary for hierarchical multiuser evaluation (G2_U6, local_20251201_234536). Updated multiple slurm HPC scripts for evaluation workflows.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Replace hierarchical detection results with multiuser performance data

Removed hierarchical and naive detection evaluation summaries and seeds, and added new multiuser performance results and summaries for hierarchical and naive schemes. Robustness evaluation results were relocated to a new directory. Updated SLURM scripts to reflect changes in evaluation workflow.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Add hierarchical and naive detection evaluation results

Added summary.json files for hierarchical and naive schemes, seeds.txt, and summary_all_configs.csv for evaluation results. Updated evaluate_multiuser_performance.py to optimize user loading and tracing, and added local runner scripts for collusion resistance, paraphrasing, rewrite, and synonym attacks.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Add hierarchical performance local evaluation script

Introduces evaluation_scripts_local/run_hierarchical_performance_local.py to run all hierarchical and naive multi-user watermarking performance configurations locally. Also updates README with usage instructions and adds support for --seeds-file in evaluation scripts for reproducible experiments.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Add local hierarchical detection and robustness scripts

Added helper scripts for running hierarchical detection and robustness evaluations locally. Improved staged tracing logic in HierarchicalMultiUserWatermarker for more efficient group and user identification. Updated .gitignore to exclude random_notes.txt. Removed PARAMS.md and random_notes.txt as obsolete documentation and notes.

recent_commits.author: NevanPham
recent_commits.message:
Centralize and deduplicate random seed management

Refactored evaluation scripts to store random seeds in a single seeds.txt file per experiment in the base output directory, ensuring seeds are only written once per configuration. Removed redundant per-run seed files and helper functions, and updated SLURM scripts to use 200 prompts instead of 300 for all runs.

Add GPT-5 support and improve log analysis token handling

Added GPT-5 and related models to the provider list and updated pipeline logic to handle them with appropriate reasoning effort. Improved log analysis agent to dynamically determine max input tokens based on model capabilities, switched token encoding to 'o200k_base', and enhanced logging and preprocessing for better performance and clarity. Updated database agent and log analysis utilities for consistent tokenization. Minor prompt and output formatting adjustments.
